-- Kumba Iron Ore Says It Agreed to Increase Workers' Salaries as Much as 10%
-- B y   V e r n o n   W e s s e l s
-- 2010-10-05T06:17:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-05/kumba-iron-ore-says-it-agreed-to-increase-workers-salaries-as-much-as-10-.html
Kumba Iron Ore Ltd. agreed to pay
increases of 7.5 percent, 9 percent and 10 percent across the
different categories in the company, itsaid in an e-mailed
statement dated yesterday.  The wage offer includes a 0.5 percent safety increment
based on 2009 performance, the Johannesburg-based company said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Vernon Wessels at 
 vwessels@bloomberg.net  